Paper: hep-th/9611173

Date: 1996-11-21

Title: Super D-branes

Authors: E. Bergshoeff and P.K. Townsend

Comments: 27pp. Typos corrected. To appear in Nucl. Phys. B

Journal-ref: Nucl.Phys. B490 (1997) 145-162

We present a manifestly Lorentz invariant, spacetime supersymmetric, and`$\kappa$-invariant' worldvolume action for all type II Dirichlet p-branes,$p\le9$, in a general type II supergravity background, including massivebackgrounds in the IIA case. The $p=0,2$ cases are rederived from D=11. The$p=9$ case provides a supersymmetrization of the D=10 Born-Infeld action.